g.aria-label: Input MIDI notes trigger the envelope controlling the cutoff of both filters

Filter internals can be rerouted using this set of 64 knobs, causing unpredictable effects. They are grouped into four quadrants related to source and destination of the signal. The left column bends only the first filter, the right column bends only the second filter and the bottom row makes signal leak between filters (cross-modulation)

Four macro knobs, each rotates all the knobs of a corresponding bending matrix quadrant. When the knob is set to the middle, the bending matrix has no effect. Rotating it clockwise or counterclockwise increases the amount of bending Recommended target for automation
Reset a quandrant to "no effect mode"
Randomize a quadrant, ensure macro knobs are not set to zero to hear the effect
AutoGain matches input and output volume. Heavy compression can cause distortion
Standard cutoff and resonance filter controls
Drive knob for input pre-amplification More drive = more overdriven sound but less self-oscillation
Mix knob: pass signal without filtering If you want to use only one filter, set Mix knob to 0 on one filter, and control the other filter
Big Bend knob macro-controls the strength of all 64 knobs in the matrix. When the knob is set to the middle, the bending matrix has no effect. Recommended to control overall madness of the sound
